oracle.mapviewer.share.ext
Class NSDataSet

java.lang.Object
  oracle.mapviewer.share.ext.NSDataSet

public class NSDataSet
extends java.lang.Object

This class represents a collection of Non-Spatial data in the form of rows and columns.
Typically it is produced by an NSDataProvider's buildDataSet() method.

setCustomRenderingRules

public void setCustomRenderingRules(RenderingRule[] customRenderingRules)
Sets the custom rendering rules for this data set. Custom rendering rules allow you to associate multiple rendering styles with multiple named columns from this NS data set. These rendering rules override what's defined for the involved theme.

Parameters:
customRenderingRules - - the custom rendering rules to use with this data set
See Also:
RenderingRule

getCustomRenderingRules

public RenderingRule[] getCustomRenderingRules()
Returns the custom rendering rules for this data set. If no special rules are needed or defined, you can simply return null here.

Returns:
renderingRule[] - array containing custom rendering rules or null if none exists.
